  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a single-centre study over 36 months for the inclusion of 30 patients. The selection
      and inclusion of patients will take place according to the criterion of Medical Termination
      of Pregnancy at 4 different gestational ages (8-12 weeks of gestation (WG)), 13-16 WG, 17-23
      WG and 25-35 WG. The tissue analysed will principally be the gonads, other somatic tissue
      will also be systematically harvested in parallel (liver and psoas muscle) for control
      purposes. The gonads will be subjected to molecular biology analyses destined to quantify the
      expression of transposons and their inhibitors.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
